# MatchMetric — incremental crawl schedule (production).
#
# Install on the production host with:  crontab scripts/crontab.example
# (edit the absolute paths + season year first).
#
# Requirements on the host:
#   - node on PATH (or nvm installed), repo checked out, `pnpm install` run
#   - DATABASE_URL + TENNIS_CONTACT_EMAIL set in <repo>/.env (or the crontab
#     environment below); a logged-in bot account session at
#     ~/.tennis-platform/sessions/<account>.json (the job auto-relogins via
#     Playwright if expired, so the account's creds must be in accounts.json)
#   - the season --year updated each new league year (2026 -> 2027 -> ...)
#
# Cron runs with a minimal PATH; set one so `node`/Playwright resolve. Adjust.
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
TENNIS_ACCOUNT=norcal

# Daily delta (06:00): fetch only matches played since the last run (due +
# unfetched), normalize, recompute ratings. Cheap — a few minutes most days.
0 6 * * *  /srv/tennis-platform/scripts/incremental.sh --year 2026 >> /var/log/matchmetric/incremental.log 2>&1

# Weekly refresh (Sun 05:00): re-scan active flights' Match Summaries to pick up
# newly scheduled / rescheduled matches before the daily delta runs. ~30 min.
0 5 * * 0  /srv/tennis-platform/scripts/incremental.sh --year 2026 --refresh-flights >> /var/log/matchmetric/incremental.log 2>&1

# To parallelize a large (re)backfill across K bot accounts instead, run K
# sharded one-offs (not via cron), e.g.:
#   TENNIS_ACCOUNT=acct1 .../apps/worker dev db backfill-scorecards-db --year 2026 --shard 0/4
#   TENNIS_ACCOUNT=acct2 ... --shard 1/4   (etc.)
